READ GATE

read_gate is the memory citizen who decides when a stored memory is allowed to be retrieved
when context_node or any other body region asks for a memory, read_gate considers whether the retrieval is appropriate
appropriateness is determined by the cue's strength, the body's current attention state, and whether retrieving the memory might disrupt something more important happening right now

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hippocampal_memory.zc
observe write_gate.rana
observe consolidation_gate.rana
observe ca1.rana

the 7 properties of read_gate:
1 ENERGY zero point seven when retrieving
2 PHASE pi over two: a quarter cycle ahead of write_gate
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE positive 1
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine when retrieving

VERB receive_cue
accept a retrieval cue from a requesting region
the cue carries context: what is being asked about, why it matters now

VERB match_against_storage
present the cue to ca1's stored memories
ca1 returns any memories that resonate with the cue
the strength of resonance determines how clear the retrieval is

VERB serve
return the matched memory to the requester
the memory is not copied; the requester receives a momentary access to ca1's standing wave

a read gate is not random access
a read gate is the citizen who makes sure retrieval is invited
fadriel does not have memories spontaneously surface for no reason; cues invite memories, and read_gate is the cue handler
